******
[2] Cholera - Malawi (Nsanje District)
Date: Tue 31 Mar 2015
Source: AllAfrica, Malawi News Agency (Lilongwe) report [summ., edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503311541.html


Cholera continues to haunt people in Nsanje, with latest reports indicating that cholera cases have hit 159, and that the outbreak has also spread to the area of Chief Mbenje. District Environmental Health Officer (DEHO) Veronica Mkukumira told Malawi News Agency Monday afternoon, 30 Mar 2015, that the situation was slowly getting out of hand. Mkukumira revealed that Kalemba and Sorgin health facilities which are in the area of Chief Mbenje have already treated 1 and 3 cases respectively.

"Things are getting out of hand as 27 cholera cases have been treated within the week bringing the numbers to 159 from 132 last week [week of 23 Mar 2015]. However the District Health Office is working around the clock fighting the cholera epidemic through health talks as well as cholera sensitization campaigns," she said.

On Mon 30 Mar 2015, the NGO, Churches Action in Relief and Development-CARD rescued the District Health Office with a donation of medical supplies including chlorine and oral rehydration salts (ORS) to help control the situation. Mkukumira was hopeful that such interventions would help control the situation. She hailed CARD for complementing government's efforts in controlling the outbreak.

[Byline: Martin Chiwanda]

